# AI Governance Controls
Enforce GOV-01 through GOV-10 at development time.
- GOV-01: Verify model is registered in Model Risk Register before deployment
- GOV-02: All AI model changes must pass pre-deployment validation pipeline
- GOV-03: Bias testing required for models affecting patient care
- GOV-04: Human override pathway required for all clinician-facing AI
- GOV-05: Explainability fields proportional to model risk class
- GOV-06: Heartbeat monitoring for accuracy drift and alert fatigue
- GOV-07: Data lineage tracking for all AI data sources
- GOV-08: Vendor accountability terms for third-party AI
- GOV-09: AI incident response protocol for failures
- GOV-10: AI Governance Board approval for clinical deployments
